public class FactorialRecursion {

    // Recursive method to calculate factorial
    public static long factorial(int n) {
        // Base case: 0! = 1
        if (n == 0) {
            return 1;
        }
        // Recursive case: n! = n * (n - 1)!
        return n * factorial(n - 1);
    }

    // Main method
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int num = 10; // Number to calculate the factorial for
        System.out.println("Factorial of " + num + " using recursion: " + factorial(num));
    }
}
2. Factorial using Iteration:
In this approach, the factorial of a number n is calculated using a loop. The loop runs from 1 to n, multiplying each number by the current result.

public class FactorialIteration {

    // Iterative method to calculate factorial
    public static long factorial(int n) {
        long result = 1;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            result *= i;
        }
        return result;
    }

    // Main method
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int num = 10; // Number to calculate the factorial for
        System.out.println("Factorial of " + num + " using iteration: " + factorial(num));
    }
}
